assetDescriptions.description: The Berkshire Running Camp is a truly unique experience, providing runners with all of the training, teambuilding, and leadership tools to become better runners, teammates, and young men and women. In addition to our outstanding training regimen, which we will work into the runners' summer training programs, athletes will communicate with our staff and one another during small group sessions to discuss all of the components of being the best runners they can be. In addition, there will be teambuilding adventure activities each day to unlock the leadership potential for each athlete.

organization.organizationDsc: The Berkshire Running Camp want to help make you a different runner. A faster, stronger, smarter runner. A better teamate, a better leader, a better person. Join us in the Berkshire mountains for a week of training the body and mind. Experience the Difference~ BRC

Sports enrichment programs specializing in ages 2-10 years of age! 

Greater Boston Area! 

 

Welcome to HERO Kids Sports.
Our promise: Fitness, Nutrition, Friends & Fun!

We have devised a specialized program that coaches kids in the fundamentals of their chosen sport, one step at a time.

Every program is specifically designed to teach your child the fundamentals of the sport and to learn how to be part of a team. We emphasize that no HERO works alone and can only succeed through helping others. 

Our programs start out with warm up sessions designed to teach children how to properly  prepare for exercise. Each week marks the completion of a new milestone in the basics of the sport. Join our HERO Kids Sports team today! 

HERO Kids Sports currently hosts 8 different sports for a period of six weeks at a time. We come to you and your kid at the school that they attend! 

If you do not see a sport that you would love to get your kid involved in, just let us know and we will work out the rest! Below is a brief description of each of the sports. For a more detailed breakdown of what each week entails, please contact us directly!

What HERO Believes:
• Hero Kids Sports believes every child can succeed in life by developing confidence, motivation and a sense of belonging.
• All kids are capable and have the ability to be good at sports; they just need a little encouragement to learn.
• Younger, brighter minds! Our unique focus is 2-10 years of age. We know from years of experience of working with kids that the earlier kids start in sports, the more fun they have and the more they want to learn!

What HERO Does:
• We come to your school, park, house or residence to teach kids the fundamentals of sports.
• Through a unique child-focused introduction to team sports, we provide exceptional education in an inspiring atmosphere.
• HERO Kids Sports equips kids with the basics of a variety of athletics so that everyone can play as a team.
• Our program connects the essential components of a healthy life: being fit, eating healthy, having friends and feeling successful.

 

We are currently operating in the greater Boston area. Contact us directly by phone or email to find out if HERO is at your kid’s school!

assetDescriptions.description:
Against the Tide is a multi-sport event in support of the Massachusetts Breast Cancer Coalition. This inspiring, family-friendly event includes USATF-certified 5K and 10K runs, along with competitive and recreational 1 mile swims, a 2 mile kayak, a 3 mile fitness walk and an Aquathon. All proceeds benefit the Massachusetts Breast Cancer Coalition's mission of breast cancer prevention.

Event details and schedule

Event Schedule:

Please note that awards will be presented throughout the morning.

7:00AM   -- Registration Opens. Please plan to visit the registration tent at least 1 hour in advance of the first event activity you will be participating in.

8:30AM   -- 1 mile Competitive Swim/Aquathon

8:30AM   -- USATF Certified 5K/10K Runs

8:50AM   -- 3 mile Walk

9:45AM   -- 1 mile Recreational Swim

10:45AM  -- 2 mile Kayak

11:30AM  -- Closing Ceremony

assetDescriptions.description:
The 5th Annual Brian McSharry Memorial Walk/Run will be taking place August 20th 2016 at D.W. Filed Park in Brockton, MA. This 6.2 K walk or run will take you through one side of the park completing a loop, starting and ending at the top of the hill by the observation tower. The top three finishers per category will receive awards. We will also have raffles for prizes as well as a 50/50 raffle.

This is a fun family event, strollers and dogs welcomed. All proceeds from the event go towards a scholarship at Massasoit Community College for a student in the criminal justice field.

Event details and schedule

Registration and Packet pick up: 8:15 am

Runners start: 9:00 am

Walkers start: 9:15 am

Parking is available at the top of the hill inside the gates.

assetComponents.assetName: Police, Veterans, and Fire Fighters - Individual Age group/open

assetDescriptions.description:
The Hillside Restoration project & the Boylston Parks & Recreation Department will hold their 3nd annual Cold Water Run 5K trail run on Sunday, August 21st  at 8:30am at Hillside.  This event commemorates John B. Gough's legacy as one of the most important social reformers of the 19th century.  This run will also celebrate Gough's Birthday (August 22nd, 1817 in Kent, England)  The 5K Trail run will wind through the Hillside Estate on the trails surrounding Gough's 1848 house, which in it's day was a 100-acre working farm.  The 5K largely follows cross-country courses that were used several years ago by local colleges and universities to host meets.

Check in starts at 7:30am on the lawn of the Gough House. The address is 215 Main Street Boylston, MA  01505

Birthday Cake, along with other food and drinks will be served during the post-run party on the lawn of the Gough House.

Awards will be given for overall and age group winners.

Event details and schedule

Check in Starts at 7:30am on the front lawn of the Gough House.

There is plenty of parking on site.  Volunteers will be on hand to direct you where to go.

This is a timed race by Central Mass Striders.

This is a Trail run that will take you through hills, open fields, and wooded trails.

This event is presented by NM Cares 501(c)3 Outreach organization raising awareness on the abuse and misuse of opioids and help.

Entry Fee

Ages 19 & up: $25.
18 & under: $15.
Day-of Registration: $20 for 18-under / $30 for 19+.

results.assetName: NM Cares 3.6 Mile Road Race - "Ending the Stigma....Starting New Lives"

assetDescriptions.description:
This Two-Mile Run/Walk starts and finishes at the Village Green in Hyannis.
The Barnstable Police Department is putting on this event to benefit: Cops For Kids With Cancer.

Entry Fee

$20.00 January 11-June 30
$22.50 July 1-July 31
$25.00 August 1-Race Day
Youth 6 and under free, 7-12 $10.00, 13-18 $15.00.

Awards

Prizes to First Place male and female runners and walkers and to first-third in age groups.
Awards at the Village Green immediately following the event.
All youth 12 and under receive a medal.

Age Groups

13-20, 21-29,30-39, 40-49,50-59, 60- 69, 70 -79, 80 plus.
